    "Generally, text of failure documents is considered to provide more information as a prompt compared to the sub-graphs.",
    "However, because failure documents are written in natural language, they likely contain a lot of information that could be considered noise.",
    "Therefore, the proportion of interpretable information from failure documents is likely smaller compared to that of the sub-graphs by the LLM.",
    "Additionally, the difference in the distribution of interpretable information between the subgraphs and failure documents suggests that providing both sources of information in the prompt results in the highest score.",
    "In summary, these explanations can be represented as shown in Fig. 6."
